REFLECTION
The group decided on a purpose of the meeting which was about upgrading operating systems and core software. 
Then the IT manager (Julian) structured an agenda with prioritized topics, and inviting only necessary participants. 
At first, we decided how the meeting would go during our last in-person meeting. 
At last, we decided to do it in a Google Meet room to discuss our important subtopics regarding the meeting, we chose the time which works for all the members of the team
, and assigned the roles to each member. 
The group then set a flow around the categories of the items to be discussed. 
Finally, we followed the outline/flow we constructed for the meeting which deemed effective.

One challenge we encountered was that one of our members was 
non-participative no matter how many times we attempted to contact him to partake in the meeting.

Collaborating with your peers or your team online can help boost productivity even with the same peers being far away, it gives teams 
an opportunity to connect and discuss about topics, exchange knowledge, and overcome communication challenges in the digital space.
